The article is a readout of President Obama's meeting with members of Congress on the situation in Libya. The President provided an update on the accomplishments so far, including the transfer of enforcement of the no-fly zone to NATO and the agreement for NATO to assume command and control of the civilian protection component. The meeting lasted for about an hour and included members from both parties in both the House and Senate. Various administration officials, including Chief of Staff Bill Daley, National Security Advisor Tom Donilon, and Secretary of State Hillary Clinton (via phone), were also present.